[div class=p 
	"Verifying a 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=TAS|href=/Glossary#ToolAssistedSpeedrunTas)
	" on a real console starts with a TAS 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=movie file|href=/Glossary#EmulatorMovieFile)
	" (often converted to a suitable format using a 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext="dump script"|href=/ConsoleVerification/Guide#Scripts)
	") and a 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=replay device|href=/ConsoleVerification/Guide#ReplayDevices)
	" that emulates a controller. The process is similar to a player piano where turning on the console prompts the controller (the replay device) for the first set of button presses, then the second, and so on from the beginning of the movie to the end with the result that the entire movie file originally produced in an 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=emulator|href=/EmulatorResources)
	" is played back on a physical console. TAS movies that have been verified this way are referred to as 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=console verified movies|href=/ConsoleVerification/Movies)
	" and are denoted with a 
	[img class=embed mw-100 src=/images/verified.png 
	]img
	".
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"The process of performing a console verification is described on the 
	(__wikiLink|href=/ConsoleVerification/Guide|implicitdisplaytext=ConsoleVerification/Guide)
	" page.
]div
